      "notes": "Latest case note 2026-02-10: Initial meeting / job search assistance + remote work focus + veteran resources (VR&E) Participant met with staff to discuss employment goals and services available through the American Job Center. Participant reported being unemployed since approx. April of last year after a contracting position with the Department of Homeland Security ended abruptly. Participant prefers remote work at this time due to family situation (infant ~7 months; spouse employed) and to reduce stress; open to in- person/hybrid if ideal opportunity arises. Participant background: administrative / executive assistant experience; Bachelor ’ s degree in Psychology . Participant indicated interview anxiety (especially phone interviews ), but reports typically able to secure jobs once interviewed. Preferences/constraints discussed: • Work setting: Remote preferred; hybrid considered (Nashville acceptable if needed); local Clarksville preferred • Commute: Ideal 10-15 minutes (Clarksville area); willing to consider further for strong opportunity • Schedule: Prefers start time after 9:00 AM ; otherwise open • Employment timeline: Open to starting within next couple of weeks • Support needs: Job leads/referrals; optional interview practice; resume support as needed (participant feels resume is generally okay) Veteran-related discussion: Participant reported VA disability rating (30%) and interest in veteran benefits/resources. Staff provided guidance on VA Veteran Readiness & Employment (VR&E) program and encouraged participant to apply online; explained VR&E process (orientation/counseling, plan development, potential training/education support). Staff also encouraged participant to explore increasing claim/rating as appropriate and offered to send resources. Job search activity/assistance provided: Staff demonstrated JOBS4TN job search functions including: • using filters (date posted, “ remote ” where available, occupation groups) • reviewing postings and saving/ “ pinning ” items for quick access • explained Virtual Recruiter/Saved Search and notification options (app + email) and limitations of filtering strictly by remote in certain saved search setups Staff also discussed USAJOBS navigation and general best practices (keywords/scanner/targeting). Staff reviewed appropriate use of AI tools for narrowing job posting requirements and tailoring content, with caution against over- reliance. Plan/Next Steps: • Staff to send participant a recap email/message with links/resources: VR&E application info, claim/benefits resource info, and relevant job search tips. • Staff will continue to share job leads that match participant ’ s remote/admin preferences when available; participant asked to provide feedback on leads to ensure relevance and avoid spamming. • Participant encouraged to attend available AJC workshops (including remote options) and job fair opportunities. Follow-up: Participant will apply to VR&E if interested; will respond to staff messages with feedback and questions.. Initial meeting / job search assistance + remote work focus + veteran resources (VR&E) Participant met with staff to discuss employment goals and services available through the American Job Center. Participant reported being unemployed since approx. April of last year after a contracting position with the Department of Homeland Security ended abruptly. Participant prefers remote work at this time due to family situation (infant ~7 months; spouse employed) and to reduce stress; open to in- person\nStaff assisted activity records in source batch: 4.",
