          "date": "2026-02-17",
          "scenario": "60 Day Check in Veteran was contacted by phone to complete the required 60-day case management assessment. The purpose of the contact was to evaluate employment progress, review employment goals, and determine continued service needs. The veteran continues to maintain full-time employment. He reported that although his current role is manageable and stable, it does align with his long-term career goals. Labor market conditions were discussed, including the veteran ’ s observation that Data Analysis is a broad and competitive field. To increase competitiveness, training and credentialing options were explored. The Case Manager identified several free IT certification resources available to veterans, particularly in cybersecurity and cloud services, and will provide this information via email for the veteran ’ s review. The veteran will assess alignment with his long-term career progression goals. The Employment Plan was reviewed and updated as appropriate. The veteran continues to meet JVSG eligibility criteria due to a significant barrier to employment (service-connected disability). Continued DVOP services remain appropriate at this time. Action Plan: • Veteran will review provided training resources by 02/27/2026 . • Veteran will continue applying for Data Analyst positions. • Follow-up contact scheduled for 03/13/2026 to assess progress and determine next service steps. Case remains active. 02/17/2026 2876406 Follow-Up Contact - Telephone Case Management Staff conducted outreach last Friday 13 FEB 26 and left a voicemail. The veteran returned the call on Monday while the office was closed and left a message with an update. Staff successfully reconnected with the veteran by phone today. During the call, the veteran reported continued active job search efforts , including applications and interviews with A.O. Smith, AutoZone, and Advance Auto Parts. One employer reported technical issues within their hiring system and has not provided additional follow- up. Staff discussed employer review timelines and reinforced the importance of patience during hiring processes. The veteran continues to follow up with Express Employment and prefers local employment opportunities with a desired wage range in the mid-$20s to low-$30s per hour , consistent with his skills and experience. Staff affirmed that these expectations are reasonable and encouraged continued broad application efforts. The veteran reported financial stressors and limited weekly income , noting use of community food assistance resources. Staff provided encouragement and reinforced persistence with both employment and benefits processes. The veteran confirmed upcoming VA appointments in March and April 1 related to disability evaluation. Staff emphasized the importance of attending appointments and discussing symptoms based on worst- day impact to ensure accurate assessment and long-term benefit stabilization. The veteran expressed interest in future business or passive income opportunities; however, staff encouraged focus on immediate employment and VA benefit stabilization. Plan: • Veteran will continue applying and following up with employers. • Veteran will attend scheduled VA appointments. • Staff will provide additional job leads as available. • Staff will follow up within 7-10 days. Case remains active.",
