          "scenario": "VA Hiring: Employment Counselors & Specialists - Career Opportunity Dear Lance, I wanted to share an employment opportunity that may be of interest. The Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) is hiring more than 300 Employment Counselors and Vocational Rehabilitation Specialists nationwide to support the Veteran Readiness and Employment (VR&E) program. These roles focus on assisting Veterans with overcoming employment barriers, pursuing education or training, and achieving long-term career goals. Key Details: • Positions available nationwide • Application deadline: March 17 • Backgrounds encouraged: vocational rehabilitation, counseling, social work, or related fields To view and apply, please visit the VA job page below and select “ Find VRS/VRC Positions ” under Featured Positions: https://benefits.va.gov/benefits/jobs/index.asp For questions about VA benefits or eligibility, you may also contact the VA directly through Ask VA: https://ask.va.gov/ If you would like assistance reviewing the job announcement, tailoring your resume, or preparing for the application process, feel free to reach out. Respectfully, Mario McMichael Veteran Outreach Specialist TDLWD Phone: 931-648-5530 Email: mario.mcmichael@tn.gov American Job Center - Clarksville 523 Madison Street, Suite B Clarksville, TN 37040 Hours: Monday-Friday, 8:00 AM - 4:30 PM",
