          "servicesProvided": "Veteran met with DVOP for initial individualized career service. Veteran was verified as eligible for JVSG DVOP services based on a Significant Barrier to Employment (SBE), specifically a service-connected disability rated at 90%. Veteran is currently unemployed and actively seeking employment in personal training, sales, and Certified Occupational Therapy Assistant (COTA) fields. DVOP conducted a comprehensive initial assessment to evaluate employment history, current job readiness, and barriers impacting employment. Veteran identified multiple barriers including transportation limitations, financial hardship, and an expired COTA certification, which restricts access to preferred employment opportunities in the healthcare field. DVOP provided individualized career services aligned with identified barriers. Services included introduction to Jobs4TN job search tools to support independent job applications, resume assistance resources to improve competitiveness in targeted industries, and interview preparation guidance to strengthen employment outcomes. DVOP discussed potential pathways to address certification barriers, including exploration of training resources and recertification options for COTA. Supportive service referrals were introduced to assist with transportation and financial barriers impacting job search consistency. Veteran demonstrated engagement during the session and agreed to participate in ongoing DVOP case management services. Veteran consented to development and implementation of an Individual Employment Plan (IEP) to support attainment of employment goals and address identified barriers.",
          "clientAction": "",
          "cmAction": "DVOP will initiate development of a structured Individual Employment Plan (IEP) outlining short-term and long-term employment goals, including exploration of recertification options for COTA and alternative employment pathways. DVOP will provide ongoing job leads aligned with Veteran's career interests and coordinate referrals to supportive services to address transportation and financial barriers. Follow-up contact will occur within 14 days to assess progress on job applications, review IEP objectives, and determine need for additional services or referrals.",
          "nextFollowUpDate": "2026-05-05",
          "generatedNote": "Narrative: Veteran met with DVOP for initial individualized career service. Veteran was verified as eligible for JVSG DVOP services based on a Significant Barrier to Employment (SBE), specifically a service-connected disability rated at 90%. Veteran is currently unemployed and actively seeking employment in personal training, sales, and Certified Occupational Therapy Assistant (COTA) fields. DVOP conducted a comprehensive initial assessment to evaluate employment history, current job readiness, and barriers impacting employment. Veteran identified multiple barriers including transportation limitations, financial hardship, and an expired COTA certification, which restricts access to preferred employment opportunities in the healthcare field. DVOP provided individualized career services aligned with identified barriers. Services included introduction to Jobs4TN job search tools to support independent job applications, resume assistance resources to improve competitiveness in targeted industries, and interview preparation guidance to strengthen employment outcomes. DVOP discussed potential pathways to address certification barriers, including exploration of training resources and recertification options for COTA. Supportive service referrals were introduced to assist with transportation and financial barriers impacting job search consistency. Veteran demonstrated engagement during the session and agreed to participate in ongoing DVOP case management services. Veteran consented to development and implementation of an Individual Employment Plan (IEP) to support attainment of employment goals and address identified barriers. Assessment: Veteran is engaged and actively seeking employment but continues to face significant barriers related to disability, transportation, financial instability, and credential limitations. These barriers justify continued enrollment in DVOP services for individualized career support. Without targeted intervention, Veteran is at risk for prolonged unemployment due to limited access to transportation and inability to utilize prior certification. Continued DVOP involvement is necessary to provide structured guidance, barrier mitigation, and coordination of supportive and training resources aligned with IEP goals. Plan / Next Steps: DVOP will initiate development of a structured Individual Employment Plan (IEP) outlining short-term and long-term employment goals, including exploration of recertification options for COTA and alternative employment pathways. DVOP will provide ongoing job leads aligned with Veteran's career interests and coordinate referrals to supportive services to address transportation and financial barriers. Follow-up contact will occur within 14 days to assess progress on job applications, review IEP objectives, and determine need for additional services or referrals. Actions: • Conducted initial assessment of employment history, barriers, and career goals • Verified JVSG DVOP eligibility based on 90% service- connected disability (SBE) • Provided guidance on Jobs4TN job search tools and resources • Provided resume and interview preparation resources • Discussed recertification pathway for COTA credential • Introduced supportive service and training referral options • Initiated case management services and IEP development • Scheduled follow-up within 14 days"
